value.title: Michelle Obama releases closing campaign message: Vote for Biden 'like your lives depend on it'
value.excerpt: Former first lady Michelle Obama is making her closing message to Americans in a campaign video released less than one month until Election Day, imploring people to vote as she shares why she believes the stakes are so high this year.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr. reportedly wanted a family 'intervention' to stop Trump's 'crazy behaviour' at Walter Reed
value.excerpt: Donald Trump's erratic and controversial behaviour since his hospitalisation for Covid-19 has divided his family, according to a report.

value.title: Trump mounts bizarre and misleading White House return despite warnings
value.excerpt: A strongly medicated President Donald Trump bolted from his VIP hospital bubble Monday, staging a bizarre White House comeback that included an irresponsible mask removal and a reckless pronouncement there is nothing to fear from Covid-19, which has already killed 210,000 Americans.

value.title: Pence faces tall task in VP debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence faces a challenging environment in the first vice presidential debate on Wednesday, which will take place against an unprecedented backdrop of events.

value.title: A perverse POTUS’s projection: Every time Trump accuses, he reveals his own guilt

value.title: 'An embarrassment': Trump tweet angers pandemic survivors
value.excerpt: Some survivors of COVID-19 and people who have lost loved ones to the pandemic are angry over President Donald Trump's advice not to fear the disease

value.title: Michelle Obama Makes Final Pitch: 'Vote For Joe Biden Like Your Lives Depend On It'
value.excerpt: President Trump "continues to gaslight the American people by acting like this pandemic is not a real threat," Michelle Obama says in video remarks.

value.title: Don’t Underestimate Mike Pence
value.excerpt: A soothing dose of Hoosier calm might be just what the Trump campaign needed.

value.title: Biden suggests people were able to quarantine because 'some Black woman was able to stack the grocery shelf' in viral clip
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has landed in hot water over a viral clip of him suggesting why people were able to quarantine during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Biden describes the first debate as a 'clownish undertaking'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden was asked about his first debate with President Trump, and if he could stand up to his opponent in the future. He said the debate frustrated him but should have described it as a "clownish undertaking" instead of calling the president a clown.

value.title: Trump's niece, Mary, says the COVID-19 situation in the US is 'horrible' because the president sees illness as 'a display of unforgivable weakness'
value.excerpt: Mary Trump, an outspoken critic of Donald Trump, her uncle, spoke with NPR's "All Things Considered" after the president's COVID-19 diagnosis.

value.title: Trump off the air in Ohio and Iowa as polls show tight races in both states
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's campaign canceled its planned television advertising in Iowa and Ohio this week, focusing its spending on states where Trump is behind even as polls show he is neck-and-neck with Democratic challenger Joe Biden in the two Midwestern states.

value.title: Kamala Harris and Mike Pence will reportedly be separated by plexiglass in debate on Wednesday night
value.excerpt: The highest profile use of plexiglass so far this election cycle came from Democrat Jaime Harrison in his debate against Republican South Carolina Sen. Lindsey Graham.

value.title: Progressive groups launch 'We Paid More' campaign in response to Trump taxes report
value.excerpt: A coalition of progressive groups on Monday launched an initiative to make the case that the tax code is too favorable to the wealthy, after The New York Times reported last week that President Trump

value.title: Trump Campaign Says Biden Lacks 'Firsthand Experience' of Being Infected With COVID-19
value.excerpt: "Those firsthand experiences are what are going to get President Trump four more years," Trump campaign spokesperson Erin Perrine told Fox News on Monday.

value.title: Goldman's chief economist breaks down why a Biden-led blue wave would prompt an upgrade in growth forecasts
value.excerpt: Longer-term economic growth forecasts would be lifted by spending increases on infrastructure, climate, healthcare, and education, Goldman said.

value.title: Eric Trump scheduled to sit for deposition Monday in New York attorney general investigation
value.excerpt: Eric Trump, who runs day-to-day operations of the family real estate empire, is scheduled to sit for a deposition on Monday as part of the New York attorney general's investigation into whether the Trump Organization improperly inflated the value of its assets to obtain loans or tax benefits.

value.title: Joe Biden enlists artists like Ludacris, Dupri, Jeezy and Monica for voting ads in battleground states
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has tapped popular music artists like Ludacris, Monica, Jermaine Dupri and Jeezy to encourage Black citizens in battleground states to vote in the upcoming presidential election.

value.title: Who is Dr. Sean Conley, President Trump's physician?
value.excerpt: Conley, an officer in the U.S. Navy, earned his B.S. from the University of Notre Dame in 2002, according to his LinkedIn. He earned his D.O. from the Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine and is an experienced emergency physician.

value.title: Joe Biden's small business outreach shows he's ready to spark America's strongest recovery ever
value.excerpt: We need to turn this recovery into America’s renaissance, and that starts with sending Joe Biden and Kamala Harris to the White House.

value.title: Secret Service ‘Volunteered’ For Trump Drive, Lewandowski Claims
value.excerpt: An attending physician said the agents likely didn’t know the “real risks” of being inside the vehicle with Trump.

value.title: Trump pledges to pass 'THE BIGGEST TAX CUT EVER' in early morning campaign tweetstorm from Walter Reed
value.excerpt: Trump previously vowed a middle-class tax cut during the November 2018 midterms, but it never happened. His second-term tax platform remains vague.

value.title: CNN supercut shows how Trump has repeatedly mocked his opponents’ health
value.excerpt: CNN’s John Avlon on Monday showed how President Donald Trump has repeatedly used his political opponents’ health as a weapon, such as when he openly mocked Hillary Clinton for coming down with pneumonia in 2016.

value.title: Biden visits Miami's Little Havana, Haiti ahead of national town hall from key swing state of Florida
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden is expected to visit Miami’s Little Havana and Little Haiti ahead of a televised town hall Monday, as the former vice president returns to the critical swing state of Florida in the final homestretch of his election campaign.

value.title: Meadows: ‘Still optimistic’ Trump will leave hospital later on Monday
value.excerpt: Trump's chief of staff said the president will meet with his doctors and nurses on Monday morning to assess his progress.
